column3: str

<UIForeground>F201FC</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FD</UIGlow> Quest Sync<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
Kipeshpe is in need of a traveler with a little time to spare.
Deliver the freshly cut nopales and tuna to Nikawtenhe.
Deliver the freshly cut nopales and tuna to Tsanaya.
Speak with Kipeshpe.
Can't say I've seen you here before. A traveler passing through, I take it? Before you set off, would you be willing to lend me a hand?
It's a simple thing, really. Just a small delivery of nopales and tuna.
Take these to Nikawtenhe at the saloon and Tsanaya by the rroneek stables. When you're finished, come back here, and I'll see if I can't put together a little something for your troubles.
You won't have to go far─just to the saloon and the rroneek stables. I promise to make it worth your time.
Welcome, friend. If you're looking to wet your whistle, I've got just the thing.
Why, this is the nopales and tuna I ordered! I certainly wasn't expecting you to be the one to deliver it.
If you've never tried them, I highly recommend it. Removing the needles can be something of a hassle, but nopales can be used for all sorts of cooking.
And the tuna can be used for desserts if you peel them, or squeezed to make juice.
Thank you for the quick delivery.
Gods, am I thirsty...
For me? From the nopales farmer? His timing is impeccable as always.
Water-laden as they are, nopales and tuna can be lifesavers when you're traveling about the wilds.
Lucky for me, they make great feed for the rroneek, as well. My thanks for the delivery, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>miss<Else/>sir</If>.
My thanks again to the farmer. There really is nothing more refreshing than fresh nopales and tuna.
You'll not want for water on your travels with nopales in your satchel.
Your empty hands tell me you've finished making the deliveries.
And what did you think, seeing their elation for a delivery of fresh nopales? Pique your interest? Or maybe even worked up your appetite?
You'll rarely find it eaten anywhere outside of the wilds, but someday, I hope to share the joys of nopales cuisine with all of Tural─no, the world!
A far-fetched dream, perhaps, but so long as travelers like yourself happen to be passing through, that's one more person I can reach.
The next time your stomach growls with hunger, I hope you'll consider answering with fresh nopales.
